<TITLE> President calls for IT access for all </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 17 (bdnews24.com)  President Zillur Rahman on Monday called for access to information technology for all sections of people. "Information technology should not only be made available to rich people in the urban areas," he said, "the rural people should also have the access." He was speaking at a programme, marking World Telecommunication and Information Society Day, at the Bangabandhu International Conference Centre, Monday. Rahman stressed the need for creating opportunities for villagers to access the information technology, and urged bridging the villages and towns to the rest of the world for the development of people's lives. The president also called for bringing all government activities under an IT framework to ensure greater mobility, transparency and accountability. Telecommunications Minister Raziuddin Ahmed Razu and state minister for science and ICT, Yafes Osman, among others, attended the programme. bdn
